				"url": "{{translationEngineHost}}/health",
				"description": "### **Response Example**\n\n``` json\n{\n    \"status\": \"success\",\n    \"message\": \"Service is running\",\n    \"uptime\": \"2 hours 15 minutes\",\n    \"database\": \"connected\",\n    \"cdn\": \"connected\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n### **Response Fields**\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `status` | string | Indicates if the service is up (`success`) or down (`fail`) |\n| `message` | string | Human-readable status message |\n| `uptime` | string | Optional: how long the service has been running |\n| `database` | string | Status of database connection (`connected` or `disconnected`) |\n| `cdn` | string | Status of CDN (MinIO) connectivity |\n\n### **Usage**\n\n- Use in **health monitoring dashboards** or **container orchestration** (e.g., Kubernetes `livenessProbe` and `readinessProbe`).\n    \n- Can be polled by external services to **verify that the application, database, and CDN are reachable**."
			},
